---
---

<header
  id="top"
  style="position:relative; background:radial-gradient(120% 62% at 50% -8%, color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 17%, transparent), transparent 60%);"
>
  <div style="max-width:1120px; margin:0 auto; padding:128px 32px 108px;" class="section-pad">
    <div
      data-reveal
      style="font-family:'Geist Mono',monospace; font-size:12.5px; letter-spacing:0.05em; color:var(--accent); margin-bottom:30px;"
    >
      // developer relations, run by an engineer
    </div>

    <h1
      data-reveal
      class="hero-heading"
      style="font-weight:600; font-size:64px; line-height:1.04; letter-spacing:-0.035em; margin:0 0 30px; max-width:880px; color:#fafafa;"
    >
      The human side of your developer product, run by someone who can read the code.
    </h1>

    <p
      data-reveal
      style="font-size:20px; line-height:1.6; color:#9a9a9a; max-width:620px; margin:0 0 40px;"
    >
      I'm a senior frontend engineer who'd rather be talking to your developers, making the content,
      and showing up in your community than shipping another internal feature. The warm, technical
      face your product has been missing.
    </p>

    <div data-reveal class="hero-ctas" style="display:flex; gap:14px; align-items:center; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <a href="#contact" class="btn-primary">Tell me about your product</a>
      <a href="#work" class="btn-secondary">See how it works →</a>
    </div>

    <div data-reveal style="margin-top:40px; font-size:14px; color:#6f6f6f;">
      For Series A/B teams with a developer-facing product (an API, SDK, or platform) and no one
      yet owning developer adoption.
    </div>
  </div>
</header>
